sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The sequence of Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) is cloned downstream the yeast ADH1 promoter and ended with an ADH1 terminator to generate a expression cassette in yeast Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Use a constitutive promoter ADH1 to mediate the expression of reporter protein Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The expression of Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) may affect the sensing resolution of intracellular cAMP level, so creating expression cassettes with different expression level is critical for the project. This cassette is one of high expression level.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The linker sequence between ADH1 terminator and different coding sequences
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the linker sequence between ADH1 terminator and Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) to introduce the AvrII and AscI unique cut sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We need AvrII and AscI unique cut sites to assemble the parts together.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: The linker sequence between ADH1 promoter and Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This DNA sequence is used to link the ADH1 promoter and Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) together and introduce the restriction site for ClaI.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We add a sequence downstream the ADH1 promoter to give a space between the 5' cap and cds in the transcript, and meanwhile introduce the restriction site for ClaI.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1969000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) is a fusion protein designed by professor Nagai's group, It is a detector for changes in intracellular cAMP level.
The reporter mainly contains three parts: the enhanced yellow fluorescent protein, Venus△C10, the mutated Renilla luciferase, RLuc8△N3, and the cAMP-recognition motif of human EPAC1 with a Q270E mutation(Saito, Chang et al. 2012). The yellow flourescent part is used to increase the emitted photon number of RLuc8△N3 by a Forster resonance energy transfer (FRET) mechanism, in which the excited energy of the luminescent substrate, coelenterazine, bound to RLuc is efficiently transferred intermolecularly to the acceptor Venus△C10. The cAMP-recognition motif of human EPAC1 is flanked by two split parts of RLuc8△N3 based on the complementation of split luciferase (CSL) mechanism, thus the conformational change in cAMP-recognition motif reconstitutes the catalytic activity of the split-Luc in a target-molecule-dependent fashion. Upon binding with cAMP, the fusion protein, Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6), showed the signal increase of about 130%.
We aimed to use the reporter to detect the cAMP surge upon stimulation by ligands of G-protein coupled receptors, so cloned Nano-lantern(cAMP-1.6) downstream three kinds of promoters and navigated its expression, localization and function in yeast Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yijie Lai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is a engineered sequence created by professor Nagai and we obtained it from addgene (Plasmid #61245).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: As it contains a YFP, we don't need to add any tag to monitor its cellular localization.
